main event: Observation of a round to oval shaped object with a bright metal shine in Williams Bay, Wisconsin on 2 November 1957.
interesting points: The object was observed for 15 minutes,The object was moving west,Conclusions suggest it could have been a satellite, balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomenon, Venus was noted to be in the position of observation, The report was part of Project Blue Book documenting unidentified flying objects.
sighted object: round to oval shaped object with bright metal shine
